SIMPLE: stimulation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stimulation
<hw>Stim`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stimulatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>stimulation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of stimulating, or the state of being stimulated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The irritating action of
various agents (stimuli) on muscles, nerves, or a sensory end organ, by
which activity is evoked; especially, the nervous impulse produced by
various agents on nerves, or a sensory end organ, by which the part
connected with the nerve is thrown into a state of activity;
irritation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stimulative</ent>⟦br⟧
